                <p>From its imposing Mosaic Matrix Grille and Dragon Eye DRLs to its class-leading 810mm water wading depth and segment-first Triple Differential Lock, the Majestor is built to command attention whether it is cruising through a city or conquering a mountain trail. Pre-reservations for the Majestor officially opened on February 12, 2026, at a token amount of just Rs 41,000 on the official website, and the response has already been phenomenal. Physical showcases at dealerships begin in April 2026, with deliveries set to commence in May 2026. </p>
                <p>The team at BikeCarHub has done a deep dive into every single detail of this exciting new SUV, and this comprehensive article covers everything a potential buyer needs to know — design, performance, off-road capability, interior luxury, technology, safety, variants, and more. </p>
                <h3 class="subheading">MG Majestor 2026 — Quick Facts at a Glance</h3>
                <div class="row m-b20">
                    <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 text-center image-height"><img src="~/images/blogs/2026/march/mgmajestor/downroad.webp" alt="downroad" title="downroad" loading="lazy" /></div>
                </div>

                <p>Before diving into the details, here is a quick summary of the most important things about the MG Majestor: </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Engine: 2.0L Twin Turbo Diesel, 215 PS, 478.5 Nm</li>
                    <li>Transmission: 8-Speed Automatic</li>
                    <li>Drive Options: 4x2 and 4x4 with 10 off-road modes</li>
                    <li>Water Wading: 810 mm (Highest in Segment) </li>
                    <li>Seating: 6-Seater (Captain Seats) or 7-Seater</li>
                    <li>Pre-Reserve Amount: Rs 41,000 at www.mgmotor.co.in</li>
                    <li>Price Announcement: April 2026 | Deliveries: May 2026</li>
                </ul>

                <div class="google-ad">
                    <ins class="adsbygoogle"
                         style="display:inline-block;width:1000px;height:200px"
                         data-ad-client="ca-pub-8720291170595920"
                         data-ad-slot="6204553210">
                    </ins>
                </div>
                <script>
                    (adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});
                </script>
                <h3 class="subheading">Design and Exterior: An Imposing Stance That Turns Heads</h3>
                <div class="row m-b20">
                    <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 text-center image-height"><img src="~/images/blogs/2026/march/mgmajestor/rear.webp" alt="rear" title="rear" loading="lazy" /></div>
                </div>

                <p>The MG Majestor is the tallest, longest, and widest SUV in its segment, and that size is immediately apparent when one stands in front of it. With a length of 5,046 mm, a width of 2,016 mm, and a height of 1,870 mm riding on a 2,950 mm wheelbase, the Majestor commands the road in a way few vehicles can. </p>
                <h5 class="subheading">Mosaic Matrix Grille and Dragon Eye DRLs</h5>
                <p>The front fascia of the Majestor is one of its most distinctive design elements. The large Mosaic Matrix Grille dominates the face, flanked by sharp, vertical Dragon Eye DRLs that give the SUV an instantly recognizable signature look. These aren't just stylistic elements — they communicate authority and presence from a distance, ensuring that no matter the road or condition, the Majestor is never going unnoticed. </p>
                <h5 class="subheading">Tri Beam Headlamps</h5>
                <p>Illuminating the path ahead are the Tri Beam LED Headlamps, which feature Dual Projector lenses and a Single Reflector unit. This combination ensures excellent visibility in low-light conditions, whether the driver is navigating through a foggy mountain pass or driving through a rain-soaked city at night. </p>
                <h5 class="subheading">Connected Tail Lamps and Sporty Twin Exhaust</h5>
                <p>The rear of the Majestor is equally striking. The Connected Tail Lamps create a seamless light bar across the rear, leaving a lasting impression of sophistication and modernity. At the bottom, the Sporty Twin Exhaust Tips hint at the performance lurking underneath, blending form with function beautifully. </p>
                <h5 class="subheading">Dual Shade Alloy Wheels — Largest in Segment</h5>
                <p>The Majestor rides on 265/55/R19 (48.26 cm) Dual Shade Multi-spoke Alloy Wheels, which are the largest in the segment. These wheels not only look phenomenal but also provide the stability and ground clearance needed for serious off-road adventures. </p>
                <h5 class="subheading">Colour Options</h5>
                <p>The Majestor is available in four carefully chosen shades that reflect its character perfectly: Metal Black, Pearl White, Concrete Grey, and Metal Ash. Each colour adds its own personality to the already commanding silhouette, allowing buyers to choose an expression that suits their style. </p>
                <div class="google-ad">
                    <ins class="adsbygoogle"
                         style="display:inline-block;width:1000px;height:200px"
                         data-ad-client="ca-pub-8720291170595920"
