                </script>
                <h3 class="subheading">Off-Road Capability: The 4x4 Dominator</h3>
                <div class="row m-b20">
                    <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 text-center image-height"><img src="~/images/blogs/2026/march/mgmajestor/tyre.webp" alt="tyre" title="tyre" loading="lazy" /></div>
                </div>

                <p>The MG Majestor was not designed to be just a road presence — it was built to conquer terrain. The 4x4 variant of the Majestor comes with one of the most comprehensive off-road packages ever offered in this price segment in India. </p>
                <h5 class="subheading">M-HUB: The Off-Road Command Center</h5>
                <p>At the heart of the Majestor's off-road system is the M-HUB, MG's intelligent off-road management platform. This suite does not just manage 4x4 capabilities — it unlocks the vehicle's true off-road potential, allowing drivers to navigate and conquer any terrain with confidence. The dual rotary dial setup in the cabin allows quick and intuitive switching between drive modes and 4WD settings. </p>
                <h5 class="subheading">Advanced 4x4 with 10 Off-Road Modes</h5>
                <p>The Majestor offers a remarkable 10 specialized terrain modes, covering virtually every surface a driver might encounter: </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Normal Mode (2H | AUTO | 4H | 4L) </li>
                    <li>Sand Mode (4H) </li>
                    <li>Mud Mode (4H | 4L) </li>
                    <li>Snow Mode (AUTO | 4L) </li>
                    <li>Rock Mode (4L) </li>
                </ul>
                <p>This comprehensive suite ensures supreme control from sand dunes to deep mud tracks and rocky mountain trails. </p>
                <h5 class="subheading">Segment-First Triple Differential Lock</h5>
                <p>One of the most headline-grabbing features of the Majestor is its segment-first Triple Differential Lock, covering the Front, Rear, and Centre differentials. This means that when the going gets really tough — think deep ruts, broken rock surfaces, or uneven off-road ledges — the Majestor can lock all three differentials simultaneously, delivering unyielding traction across all four wheels. No competitor in this segment currently offers this level of mechanical off-road hardware. </p>
                <h5 class="subheading">Segment-First M-Crawl System</h5>
                <p>The Majestor also features M-Crawl, another segment-first technology that transforms tricky terrain by intelligently managing both throttle and braking while the driver simply focuses on steering. This feature ensures that even less experienced off-road drivers can confidently navigate challenging obstacles, as the car does the hard work of maintaining consistent low-speed traction automatically. </p>
                <h5 class="subheading">810mm Water Wading — Highest in Segment</h5>
                <p>Perhaps the most impressive statistic of all is the Majestor's water wading capability. It can ford water up to 810 mm in depth, which is the highest in its segment. This means crossing flooded roads during monsoon, fording rivers during adventure trips, or driving through waterlogged city streets is well within the Majestor's comfort zone. </p>
                <h3 class="subheading">Powertrain and Performance</h3>
                <p>Powering the MG Majestor is a 2.0-litre Twin Turbo Diesel engine that produces 158 kW (215 PS) of power and a robust 478.5 Nm of torque — and this output remains consistent across both the 2WD and 4WD variants. The engine is paired with an 8-Speed Automatic Transmission (8AT) that delivers smooth, confident gear changes whether in city traffic or on a high-speed highway run. </p>
                <p>The combination of high torque and a proper ladder frame chassis means the Majestor is equally capable of towing heavy loads and tackling off-road terrain, making it a truly versatile vehicle for both adventure seekers and family road-trippers alike. </p>
                <p>The High Tensile Ladder Frame Chassis is a key component here, providing the rigidity and strength needed to handle the stresses of serious off-road use while also ensuring a stable, confident on-road driving experience. The front suspension uses a Double Wishbone Independent setup, while the rear gets a Five Link Integral Suspension — a setup designed to balance comfort and handling across diverse road conditions. </p>
