                                The MG Majestor has several advantages over the Toyota Fortuner and Isuzu MU-X. It is the largest in the segment (tallest, widest, longest), offers the highest water wading depth at 810 mm, comes with a segment-first Triple Differential Lock and M-Crawl system, includes 10 off-road modes, and packs significantly more interior technology and comfort features including the JBL Studio 12 system, 8-Mode Massage Seats, 220V power outlet, and ADAS Level 2. The Fortuner and MU-X are well-established, reliable products, but in terms of feature count and off-road hardware, the Majestor sets a new benchmark for this category.
